This paper compares different software packages for causal inference on linear Gaussian data, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The focus is on structure learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that deals with discovering the underlying causal relationships between variables (cs.LG). The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to the subfield of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The comparison of time performance suggests that the algorithms may involve optimization and search techniques, which are relevant to the subfield of computational optimization and information theory (cs.SI, cs.IT).
